paragraph: Jan Vyčítal (8 March 1942 – 1 March 2020) was a Czech country music singer and songwriter. He was founding member of Greenhorns. He also drew the cover art for many albums.
Vyčítal was born in Prague, Protectorate of Bohemia and Moravia. He died on March 1, 2020, at the age of 77.
